name: Plastic Whale
text: @Tommy72166557 @Iamsterdam Reduce, re-use, recycle! We totally agree. We have to change the way we consume, away from single-use and disposables. Some circularity is part of that. Great job on the machine, we wish you all the success in the world!

name: Plastic Whale
text: @Tommy72166557 @Iamsterdam We also have to reduce, for sure, but by itself that's not enough. We have so much plastic already in circulation and we buy more plastic all the time. We also need to take plastic out of our nature and re-use the plastic that has already been made, else we're doubling emissions

name: Plastic Whale
text: @Tommy72166557 @Iamsterdam Hi Tommy. Making new things is exactly what allows us to keep that plastic OUT of our nature. All the plastic we use for boats and furniture was waste, floating in the canals. We collect it, keep the canals clean, and keep the plastic out of furnaces and landfills ‚ôªÔ∏è üòÉ

name: Plastic Whale
text: @keawijkstra @SvVeldhoven Absolutely, recycling alone will not fix the problem. We do believe it is part of the solution, however. Reduce, re-use and recycle, right? The table is part of that, it has a story, it creates awareness for anyone who sits around it. That leads to more than recycling üåç ‚ôªÔ∏è

name: Plastic Whale
Plastic Whale
text: @keawijkstra @SvVeldhoven Every bottle that went into this table was fished out of the Amsterdam canals. This is not about using plastic for the sake of plastic, when better materials would do; this table is about using waste that would otherwise get thrown away and burned, sink, or go out to sea.

name: Plastic Whale
text: @clarescens @MinIenW @SvVeldhoven @Vepaoffice @NLCE2050 Reducing, re-using and recycling plastic is much more complementary than antagonistic. This table was never built to be thrown away. At the end of its life the Ministry can give it back to Plastic Whale. Is this the complete solution? No. Is it a part of the solution? Absolutely.

name: Plastic Whale
text: @vandervlies @AdmiraalHeijn @Waternet We're somewhere between neutral and pro. Our mission has always been to work ourselves out of business, we just have a different approach. Surely the days of being 100% for or against an idea, are gone?

name: Plastic Whale
text: @stevenrussell @Vepaoffice We're doing fantastic things with @Vepaoffice! Very excited for what the future will bring. All our boats are also made from recycled PET, and they all use electric motors. If you're ever in Amsterdam....

name: Plastic Whale
text: @vandervlies @AdmiraalHeijn @Waternet Absolutely not correct. We are not a political advocacy organisation, others do that better. Our role is to involve as many people as possible with a positive message. We want to tackle the same problem from a different direction (individuals and companies instead of government).
